ion'''\n| '''Seats up for election'''\n| '''Seats contested by party'''\n| '''Contested seats won'''\n| '''Contested seats lost'''\n| '''Total votes'''\n| '''Share of votes'''\n| '''Outcome of election'''\n| '''Constituency contested'''\n| '''Party leader'''\n|-\n|[[1961 Singaporean by-election|1961]]\n|2\n|1\n|1\n|0\n|3,598\n|43.3%\n|1 seat gain from PAP\n|[[Anson Single Member Constituency|Anson SMC]]\n|[[David Saul Marshall|David Marshall]]\n|}\n\n===Parliament===\n{| class=\"sortable wikitable\"\n|-\n| align=center|'''Election'''\n| '''Seats up for election'''\n| '''Seats contested by party'''\n| '''Seats won by walkover'''\n| '''Contested seats won'''\n| '''Contested seats lost'''\n| '''Total seats won'''\n| '''Change'''\n| '''Total votes'''\n| '''Share of votes'''\n| '''Popular vote'''\n| '''Outcome of election'''\n| '''Party leader'''\n|-\n|[[1968 Singaporean general election|1968]]\n|58\n|2\n|0\n|0\n|2\n|{{Composition bar|0|58|hex={{Workers' Party of Singapore/meta/color}}}}\n|{{steady}}\n|3,049\n|13.2%\n|4.0%\n|{{N/A|No seats}}\n|Chiang Seok Keong{{ref|2|2}}\n|-\n|[[1972 Singaporean general election|1972]]\n|65\n|27\n|0\n|0\n|27\n|{{Composition bar|0|65|hex={{Workers' Party of Singapore/meta/color}}}}\n|{{steady}}\n|90,885\n|24.5%\n|12.2%\n|{{N/A|No seats}}\n|rowspan=7|[[J. B. Jeyaretnam]]{{ref|3|3}}\n|-\n|[[1976 Singaporean general election|1976]]\n|69\n|22\n|0\n|0\n|22\n|{{Composition bar|0|69|hex={{Workers' Party of Singapore/meta/color}}}}\n|{{steady}}\n|91,966\n|27.9%\n|11.5%\n|{{N/A|No seats}}\n|-\n|[[1980 Singaporean general election|1980]]\n|75\n|8\n|0\n|0\n|8\n|{{Composition bar|0|75|hex={{Workers' Party of Singapore/meta/color}}}}\n|{{steady}}\n|39,590\n|29.2%\n|6.2%\n|{{N/A|No seats}}\n|-\n|[[1984 Singaporean general election|1984]]\n|79\n|15\n|0\n|1\n|14\n|{{Composition bar|1|79|hex={{Workers' Party of Singapore/meta/color}}}}\n|{{increase}}1\n|110,939\n|41.9%\n|12.7%\n|{{no2|Largest opposition}}\n|-\n|[[1988 Singaporean general election|1988]]\